On the second day , there was one of my friend(let's call Cassy)suddenly cried when the teacher was teaching. We all looking at her and the teacher even asked her whether she's okay or not . She kept repeating the same phrase which is " He's here !".  I had to admit , I got excited and scared but idk why(lmao). The next day ,she was absent but there were some of my classmates got scratched and I got it too . I still remembered,  my friend and I were very scared,we even prayed to God . I'm going to skip some of the part because the story is too long. So we found this octopus doll at our school and Cassie started to cry and act like a psycho.  My friend Amy was really quiet tha lately . We found some blood and some of my classmate even started to seeing things . We were very scared to go to school . The teacher knew what happened but she didn't want to tell us . After this paranormal thingy happened multiple of time , our principal called the priest and he doing his things .( ya'll know what I referred) After that , things were getting better than before but unfortunately my friend Amy has serious mental health right now which is is depression. After that things happened,  she kept thinking about suicide thought (she's better now at least) I didn't tell y'all her part of the story because it will be sooo long but her part was the scariest.  Y'all can say my story is fake or nah but this was based on true story and I experienced it . Idk whether it because of the "Candy Man" but yeah . snippet.textDisplay:
I never understood, nor do I think I will ever understand Hollywood's obsession with the supernatural: whether they be fictional or based on actual events.

What I mean is, in all these scary death-defying or near-death experience where the protaganist(s) are faced with a supernatural entity, they either die horrible deaths or they think they won the battle against the spirit(s) but the movie still ends in a horror cliffhanger. Fuck.

Why don't they just get on their knees and pray for strenght and protection against those evil spirits? Why won't they call out on Jesus to save them? Better to call on Jesus and let Him save you than die and suffer in eternal bloody damnation.
